        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 7:13PM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 713 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Montrose, or 8 miles west of Clinton, moving east
at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clinton, Deepwater, Coal, Brownington, Tightwad, Hartwell, La Due,
and Truman Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Missouri.</instruction>
